{"title_page": "2014\u201315 CEV Women's Challenge Cup", "text_new": "{{Infobox sports season\n| title            = 2014\u201315 CEV Women's Challenge Cup\n| league           = [[CEV Women's Challenge Cup]]\n| sport            = [[Volleyball]]\n| logo             = \n| pixels           = \n| caption          = \n| duration         = 25 October 2014 \u2013 12 April 2015\n| no_of_matches    = 96\n| no_of_teams      = 49 \n| attendance       = \n| season           = \n| season_champs    =\n| MVP              =\n| MVP_link         =\n| top_scorer       =\n| playoffs         =\n| playoffs_link    =\n| playoffs_MVP     =\n| finals           = Finals\n| finals_link      =\n| finals_champ     = {{flagicon|TUR}} [[Bursa B\u00fcy\u00fck\u015fehir Belediyespor Women's Volleyball|Bursa BBSK]]\n| finals_runner-up = {{flagicon|RUS}} [[VC Uralochka-NTMK Yekaterinburg|Uralochka-NTMK Ekaterinburg]]\n| finals_MVP       = {{flagicon|TUR}} [[Meryem \u00c7al\u0131k|Meryem Boz]]\n| finals_MVP_link  =\n| seasonslist      =\n| seasonslistnames = CEV Women's Challenge Cup\n| prevseason_link  = 2013\u201314 CEV Women's Challenge Cup\n| prevseason_year  = 2013\u201314\n| nextseason_link  = 2015\u201316 CEV Women's Challenge Cup\n| nextseason_year  = 2015\u201316\n}}\n\nThe '''2014\u201315 CEV Women's Challenge Cup''' was the 35th edition of the European [[CEV Women's Challenge Cup|Challenge Cup]] volleyball club tournament, the former \"CEV Cup\".\n\n==Format==\nThe tournament was played on a [[Knockout tournament|knockout format]], originally a total of 51 teams were to participate, due to withdraws a total of 49 teams participated. Initially 35 teams were allocated vacancies to enter the competition at the 'Qualification phase', with another 14 teams (after 2 teams withdraw) joining from the [[2014\u201315 Women's CEV Cup|Women's CEV Cup]] entering the competition at the 'Main phase' stage (as per 'Round composition' below).<ref name=DOL>{{cite web |url=http://www.cev.lu/NewsImages/17659/Files/_2015%20CEV%20Volleyball%20Cup%20and%202015%20CEV%20Volleyball%20Challenge%20Cup%20Drawing%20of%20Lots%20-%20WOMEN.pdf |title=2015 CEV Volleyball Challenge Cup Drawing of Lots - WOMEN |work=[[European Volleyball Confederation|CEV]]|accessdate=20 March 2017}}</ref><ref name=CEVCup>{{cite web |url=http://www.cev.lu/Competition-Area/competition.aspx?ID=740&PID=-2 |title=2015 CEV Cup Final Standing |work=[[European Volleyball Confederation|CEV]] |accessdate=20 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180506123455/http://www.cev.lu/Competition-Area/competition.aspx?ID=740&PID=-2 |archive-date=6 May 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nOn 12 June 2014, a drawing of lots in [[Luxembourg City]], [[Luxembourg]], determined the team's pairing for each match. Each team played a home and an away match with result points awarded for each leg (3 points for 3\u20130 or 3\u20131 wins, 2 points for 3\u20132 win, 1 point for 2\u20133 loss). After two legs, the team with the most result points advanced to the next round. In case the teams were tied after two legs, a {{em|Golden Set}} was played immediately at the completion of the second leg. The Golden Set winner is the team that first obtains 15 points, provided that the points difference between the two teams is at least 2 points (thus, the Golden Set is similar to a tiebreak set in a normal match).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cev.lu/Competition-Area/Competition.aspx?ID=741&PID=-1|title=2015 CEV Volleyball Challenge Cup - Women - Format|website=[[European Volleyball Confederation|CEV]]|accessdate=19 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140922020315/http://www.cev.lu/Competition-Area/competition.aspx?ID=741&PID=-1|archive-date=22 September 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cev.lu/Competition-Area/CompetitionNews.aspx?ID=741&NewsID=17659&TagType=0&TagContent=0&NewsType=0&Paging=3&Sd=1/1/1900&Ed=1/1/1900|title=European Cups DOL sets stage for exciting season ahead|website=[[European Volleyball Confederation|CEV]]|date=12 June 2014|accessdate=19 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n;Round composition\n* 1st Round: 6 teams\n* 2nd Round: 1st Round winners (3 teams) + 29 teams\n* 16th Final: 2nd Round winners (16 teams) + 14 teams from [[2014\u201315 Women's CEV Cup#16th Final|CEV Cup]]\n* 8th Final onwards: winners\n\n==Participating teams==\n*A total of 49 teams participated, 35 were allocated direct places and 14 joined from the [[2014\u201315 Women's CEV Cup|Women's CEV Cup]] entering at the 'Main phase'.<ref name=DOL/> \n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:left\"\n!rowspan=2|Country\n!colspan=3|No. teams\n!rowspan=2|Teams\n|-\n!{{Tooltip|Vac|Qualified via vacancies allocation}}\n!{{Tooltip|Cev|Qualified via CEV Cup}}\n!Total\n|-\n|{{AUT}}||align=\"center\"|3||align=\"center\"|2||align=\"center\"|5|| [[ASK\u00d6 Linz-Steg]]{{ref|1|1}} <br /> [[ATSC Sparkasse Klagenfurt]]{{ref|1|1}} <br /> [[SVS Post Schwechat]] <br /> [[Ti Meraner Volley Innsbruck]] <br /> [[UVC Holding Graz]]\n|-\n|{{SUI}}||align=\"center\"|2||align=\"center\"|2||align=\"center\"|4|| [[Kanti Schaffhausen]] <br /> [[Neuch\u00e2tel Universit\u00e9 Club Volleyball|Sagres Neuch\u00e2tel UC]]{{ref|1|1}} <br /> [[TSV D\u00fcdingen]] <br /> [[Volley K\u00f6niz]]{{ref|1|1}}\n|-\n|{{HUN}}||align=\"center\"|3||align=\"center\"|-||align=\"center\"|3|| [[Linamar B\u00e9k\u00e9scsabai RSE]] <br /> [[Teva G\u00f6d\u00f6ll\u00f5]] <br /> [[Vasas SC|Vasas Obuda Budapest]]\n|-\n|{{NED}}||align=\"center\"|3||align=\"center\"|-||align=\"center\"|3|| [[Alterno|Alterno Apeldoorn]] <br /> [[Sliedrecht Sport]] <br /> [[VC Sneek]]\n|-\n|{{BEL}}||align=\"center\"|2||align=\"center\"|1||align=\"center\"|3|| [[Asterix Kieldrecht]] <br /> [[VC Oudegem]] <br /> [[VDK Gent Dames]]{{ref|1|1}}\n|-\n|{{ROU}}||align=\"center\"|2||align=\"center\"|1||align=\"center\"|3|| [[CSM Bucure\u0219ti (women's volleyball)|C.S.M. Bucure\u0219ti]] <br /> [[CSU T\u00e2rgu Mure\u0219]] <br /> [[CS Dinamo Bucure\u0219ti (women's 